               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450707-name-354" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450707-name-354" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450707-name-354" type="surname" value="AYLING,"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450707-name-354" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES AYLING, JUN</persName>
                  </hi>. I work with my father, who lives in Barnard-street, Westminster; the prisoner was in my father's service for ten months. I missed these articles, and taxed him with it—he admitted taking the penknife and the toasting-fork, and asked for mercy—the other things were found by the person in the lower part of the house where he was lodging—I had seen them safe some weeks before—here are some files and other things, all my father's—we have lost 30<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 40<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. worth of pro<lb></lb>perty, but we cannot say who is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALDWIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What words did he use? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He at first denied it, but I said they were stolen from us, I could swear to them—he said he had stolen them, and asked forgiveness—no words passed between my saying I could swear to them, and his admitting it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450707-name-355" type="witnessName">
